HTML-FORMATTING TAGS
 Create a webpage for your school and change the
background colour, text colour, FONT style, colour, size, make
it Bold, Underline, Italic, insert left and top margin.
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
SSVM
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--To change the font styles-->
<BODY bgcolor="pink" text="green" leftmargin="50"
 topmargin="100">
<B> WELCOME TO SSVM WORLD SCHOOL</B>
<I> WELCOME TO SSVM WORLD SCHOOL</I>
<FONT FACE="CHILLER" SIZE="5" COLOR="RED">
<U> WELCOME TO SSVM WORLD SCHOOL </U>
</FONT>
</BODY>
</HTML>
------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Date: HTML

PARAGRAPH TAG, BR TAG & HR TAG
(<BR> TAG is used to break the line,
<HR> TAG is used to create a horizontal line.)
 Create a webpage for your own company. Change the
PARAGRAPH alignment, insert HORIZONTAL RULER.
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
MY COMPANY
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY bgcolor="YELLOW" leftmargin="50" topmargin="50">
<FONT FACE="jokerman" SIZE="2" COLOR="BLUE">
<P ALIGN="CENTER"> COMPANY NAME </P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT"> COMPANY ADDRESS </P>
<HR SIZE="8" COLOR="GREEN" >
<P ALIGN=" JUSTIFY "> TYPE FEW LINES ABOUT YOUR
COMPANY <BR> TYPE FEW LINES </P>
<P ALIGN="RIGHT"> SPECIAL OFFERS </P>
</FONT>
</BODY>
</HTML>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: HTML
HEADING TAG & MARQUEE TAG
 Create a webpage for online shopping, use the HEADING TAG
AND MARQUEE TAG.
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
Online shopping
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="pink" leftmargin="50" topmargin="50">
<FONT FACE="CHILLER" SIZE="10" COLOR="RED">
<MARQUEE BEHAVIOR="ALTERNATE (or) SCROLL"
DIRECTION=”LEFT” BGCOLOR=”GREEN”>
WELCOME TO ONLINE SHOPPING
</MARQUEE>
</FONT>
<H1> ONLINE SHOPPING </H1>
<H2> TODAY’S OFFER </H2>
<H3> SPORTS ITEMS </H3>
<H4> KIDS SECTION </H4>
<H5> MENS SECTION </H5>
<H6> WOMENS SECTION </H6>
</BODY>
</HTML>
------------------------------------------------------------------------
4
Date: HTML
IMAGE TAG
● Create a webpage with background picture and insert an
image in the webpage.
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
PARK
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="LOCATION OF THE PICTURE\NAME
OF THE PICTURE.TYPE OF FILE">
<FONT FACE="CHILLER" SIZE="10" COLOR="RED">
<MARQUEE DIRECTION=LEFT BGCOLOR=GREEN>
ITS TIME TO PLAY
</MARQUEE>
<IMG SRC=" LOCATION OF THE PICTURE\NAME OF THE
PICTURE.TYPE OF FILE " HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=100>
</BODY>
</HTML>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date: HTML
HYPERLINK TAG
● Create a website using hyperlink tag to open another
webpage and picture.
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
LINK
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=YELLOW TEXT=RED>
LINK TO OPEN A HTML PROGRAM
<A HREF="________.HTML">
CLICK HERE FOR HTML PROGRAM
</A> <BR>
LINK TO OPEN A PICTURE
<A HREF="LOCATION OF THE PICTURE\NAME OF THE
PICTURE.TYPE OF FILE ">
CLICK HERE FOR PICTURE
</A>
</BODY>
</HTML>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DATE: HTML
LIST TAG
● Create a Html Document Using LIST Tags
(OL type may be A/a/i/I/1 UL type may be disc/ circle/ square)
<HTML> <HEAD>
<TITLE> LIST </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=ORANGE>
<CENTER>
<H1> <U> SUBJECTS AND ACTIVITIES </U> </H1>
</CENTER>
<HR SIZE=10 COLOR=BLUE>
<H4> SUBJECTS </H4>
<OL TYPE=A>
<LI>ENGLISH
<LI>LANGUAGE
<LI>MATHS
<LI>SOCIAL SCIENCE
<LI>SCIENCE
</OL>
<H4> ACTIVITES </H4>
<UL TYPE=DISC>
<LI>SWIMMING
<LI>DANCE
<LI>YOGA
<LI>GUITAR
<LI>BAND
</UL>
</BODY> </HTML>
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DATE: HTML
TABLE TAG
● Create a timetable Using TABLE Tag
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
TIMETABLE
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=PINK>
<TABLE BORDER=4 ALIGN=CENTER>
<CAPTION> TIMETABLE </CAPTION>
<TR BGCOLOR=WHITE> <TH> DAY <TH> 1 <TH> 2
<TH> 3 <TH> 4 </TR>
<TR BGCOLOR=GREEN> <TD> MONDAY <TD> MAT <TD>
ENG <TD> SCI <TD> LAN </TR>
<TR BGCOLOR=YELLOW> <TD> TUESDAY <TD> ENG <TD> P.T
<TD> SOC <TD> COM </TR>
<TR BGCOLOR=BLUE> <TD> WEDNESDAY <TD> LAN <TD> SCI
<TD> MAT <TD> LIB </TR>
<TR BGCOLOR=RED> <TD> THURSDAY <TD> SOC <TD>
MAT <TD> P.T <TD> SCI </TR>
<TR BGCOLOR=ORANGE> <TD> FRIDAY <TD> ENG <TD>
MAT <TD> SOC <TD> SCI </TR>
</BODY>
</HTML>
